quran[12]{c,v,t}:
  16,43,"And in no way did We send (even) before you, except men to whom We revealed. \"So ask the population of the Remembrance, in case you (i.e. the pagan Arabs) do not know"
  16,44,"With clear evidences and the Scriptures, (i.e., the Zubur, pl, of Zabur, usually understood to be the psalms) and We have sent down to you (i.e. the prophet) the Remembrance that you may make evident to mankind what has been sent down (ever since) and that possibly they would meditate"
  16,45,"So, are the ones who have schemed odious (deeds) secure that Allah will (not) cause the earth to cave in with them? Or that the torment will not come up to them from where they are not aware"
  16,46,Or that He will not take them (away) in their moving about? Then in no way are they able to be defiant to Him
  16,47,"Or that He will not take them (away) by constant fright? Then, surely your Lord is indeed Ever-Compassionate, Ever-Merciful"
  16,48,"And have they not regarded whatever thing (s) Allah created always conceding their shades to the right and left (sides), constantly prostrating themselves to Allah, (while) they are (utterly) abject"
  16,49,"And to Allah prostrates whatever is in the heavens and whatever is in the earth of every beast, and the Angels; and they do not wax proud"
  16,50,"They fear their Lord above them, and they perform what they are commanded. A prostration is to be performed here"
  16,51,"And Allah has said, \"Do not take to yourselves two gods. Surely He is only One God; so of Me, Me (only), then, have awe"
  16,52,"And to Him belongs whatever is in the heaven and the earth, and His is the religion lasting; so will you have piety to other than Allah"
  16,53,"And whatever favor you have, (then) it is from Allah; thereafter when adversity touches you, then Him you implore"
  16,54,"Thereafter when He lifts off the adversity, only then do a group of you associate others with their Lord"